title <size:18>Notification System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Service fires event 'order shipped'. System resolves recipients, picks channels, renders template, delivers, tracks, retries on failure."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class NotificationService <<Facade>> {
    - router : NotificationRouter
    - dispatcher : NotificationDispatcher
    - templateEngine : TemplateEngine
    - preferenceStore : UserPreferenceStore
    - rateLimiter : RateLimiter
    - deliveryTracker : DeliveryTracker
    --
    + send(request) : NotificationResult
    + sendBulk(requests) : List<NotificationResult>
    + scheduleNotification(request, sendAt) : String
    + cancelScheduled(notificationId) : void
    + getDeliveryStatus(notificationId) : DeliveryStatus
    + getUserNotifications(userId) : List<Notification>
}

note top of NotificationService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Any service (orders, payments, auth) calls
    NotificationService.send(request). This
    **Facade** coordinates template rendering,
    channel routing, rate limiting, delivery,
    retry, and tracking. Callers don't know
    about email/SMS/push internals."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: NOTIFICATION REQUEST + EVENT
' ====================================================================
class NotificationRequest {
    - eventType : EventType
    - recipientId : String
    - recipientGroup : RecipientGroup
    - payload : Map<String, Object>
    - priority : NotificationPriority
    - channelOverride : ChannelType
    - idempotencyKey : String
    --
    + getPayload() : Map<String, Object>
    + hasChannelOverride() : boolean
}

enum EventType {
    ORDER_PLACED
    ORDER_SHIPPED
    ORDER_DELIVERED
    PAYMENT_SUCCESS
    PAYMENT_FAILED
    OTP_VERIFICATION
    PASSWORD_RESET
    PROMO_CAMPAIGN
    FRIEND_REQUEST
    SYSTEM_ALERT
}

enum NotificationPriority {
    CRITICAL
    HIGH
    NORMAL
    LOW
    MARKETING
}

enum RecipientGroup {
    SINGLE_USER
    USER_SEGMENT
    ALL_USERS
    TOPIC_SUBSCRIBERS
}

note top of NotificationRequest #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - What triggers a notification?**
    "Upstream services fire events: ORDER_SHIPPED,
    PAYMENT_FAILED, OTP_VERIFICATION, etc.
    **NotificationRequest** carries: event type,
    recipient (single/segment/all), dynamic
    payload (orderId, amount), priority, and
    an idempotencyKey (prevent duplicates)."
end note

NotificationRequest --> EventType
NotificationRequest --> NotificationPriority
NotificationRequest --> RecipientGroup


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: NOTIFICATION MODEL
' ====================================================================
class Notification {
    - notificationId : String
    - recipientId : String
    - channel : ChannelType
    - subject : String
    - body : String
    - status : DeliveryStatus
    - priority : NotificationPriority
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - sentAt : LocalDateTime
    - deliveredAt : LocalDateTime
    - readAt : LocalDateTime
    - retryCount : int
    - metadata : Map<String, String>
    --
    + markSent() : void
    + markDelivered() : void
    + markRead() : void
    + markFailed(reason) : void
}

enum DeliveryStatus {
    PENDING
    QUEUED
    SENT
    DELIVERED
    READ
    FAILED
    BOUNCED
    SUPPRESSED
}

enum ChannelType {
    EMAIL
    SMS
    PUSH
    IN_APP
    WHATSAPP
    SLACK
    WEBHOOK
}

note top of Notification #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - The notification object.**
    "Each delivery attempt creates a Notification
    with channel, content, status, timestamps.
    Status lifecycle: PENDING -> QUEUED -> SENT
    -> DELIVERED -> READ (or FAILED/BOUNCED).
    7 channel types — extensible."
end note

Notification --> ChannelType
Notification --> DeliveryStatus
Notification --> NotificationPriority


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: TEMPLATE ENGINE — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class TemplateEngine {
    - templates : Map<TemplateKey, NotificationTemplate>
    - renderer : TemplateRenderer
    --
    + render(eventType, channel, payload) : RenderedContent
    + registerTemplate(key, template) : void
}

class TemplateKey {
    - eventType : EventType
    - channel : ChannelType
    - locale : String
}

class NotificationTemplate {
    - templateId : String
    - subjectTemplate : String
    - bodyTemplate : String
    - channel : ChannelType
    - locale : String
    --
    + getSubject() : String
    + getBody() : String
}

class RenderedContent {
    - subject : String
    - body : String
    - htmlBody : String
    - attachments : List<String>
}

interface TemplateRenderer <<Strategy>> {
    + render(template, payload) : RenderedContent
}

class HandlebarsRenderer {
    + render(template, payload) : RenderedContent
}

class FreemarkerRenderer {
    + render(template, payload) : RenderedContent
}

class SimpleTextRenderer {
    + render(template, payload) : RenderedContent
}

note bottom of TemplateRenderer #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - Render the content.**
    "Same event, different channels need
    different templates. ORDER_SHIPPED email
    is HTML-rich. SMS is 160 chars. Push is
    title + body."

    "**Strategy Pattern** — rendering engine
    is pluggable: Handlebars for rich HTML,
    SimpleText for SMS, Freemarker for complex.
    Templates stored per (event + channel + locale)."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

TemplateRenderer <|.. HandlebarsRenderer
TemplateRenderer <|.. FreemarkerRenderer
TemplateRenderer <|.. SimpleTextRenderer
TemplateEngine --> TemplateRenderer : delegates >
TemplateEngine --> TemplateKey : indexed by >
TemplateEngine --> NotificationTemplate : stores >
TemplateEngine --> RenderedContent : produces >
NotificationService --> TemplateEngine


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: CHANNEL ROUTING — Chain of Responsibility + User Prefs
' ====================================================================
class NotificationRouter {
    - preferenceStore : UserPreferenceStore
    - handlerChain : RoutingHandler
    --
    + resolveChannels(request) : List<ChannelType>
}

abstract class RoutingHandler <<Handler>> {
    # nextHandler : RoutingHandler
    --
    + setNext(handler) : RoutingHandler
    + {abstract} handle(request, channels) : List<ChannelType>
}

class PriorityRoutingHandler {
    + handle(request, channels) : List<ChannelType>
}

class UserPreferenceHandler {
    - preferenceStore : UserPreferenceStore
    --
    + handle(request, channels) : List<ChannelType>
}

class ChannelOverrideHandler {
    + handle(request, channels) : List<ChannelType>
}

class QuietHoursHandler {
    + handle(request, channels) : List<ChannelType>
}

class UserPreferenceStore {
    - preferences : Map<String, UserPreference>
    --
    + getPreference(userId) : UserPreference
    + updatePreference(userId, pref) : void
}

class UserPreference {
    - userId : String
    - enabledChannels : Set<ChannelType>
    - mutedEventTypes : Set<EventType>
    - quietHoursStart : LocalTime
    - quietHoursEnd : LocalTime
    - locale : String
    --
    + isChannelEnabled(ch) : boolean
    + isEventMuted(event) : boolean
    + isQuietHours(now) : boolean
}

note bottom of RoutingHandler #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Which channels? (KEY STEP)**
    "OTP must go via SMS+Email. Promo only if
    user opted in. No push during quiet hours."

    "**Chain of Responsibility:**
    1. **PriorityHandler**: CRITICAL -> all channels.
       OTP -> SMS+Email forcefully.
    2. **UserPreferenceHandler**: filter by user's
       enabled channels and muted events.
    3. **ChannelOverrideHandler**: if caller forced
       a specific channel, use it.
    4. **QuietHoursHandler**: suppress push/SMS
       during 10pm-8am (except CRITICAL)."

    "Each handler refines the channel list.
    Add GDPRConsentHandler? Insert in chain."
    **Pattern: Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP**
end note

RoutingHandler <|-- PriorityRoutingHandler
RoutingHandler <|-- UserPreferenceHandler
RoutingHandler <|-- ChannelOverrideHandler
RoutingHandler <|-- QuietHoursHandler
RoutingHandler o--> RoutingHandler : next >
NotificationRouter --> RoutingHandler : uses chain >
NotificationRouter --> UserPreferenceStore
UserPreferenceStore --> UserPreference
NotificationService --> NotificationRouter


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: CHANNEL PROVIDERS — Strategy Pattern (CORE)
' ====================================================================
interface ChannelProvider <<Strategy>> {
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
    + isHealthy() : boolean
}

class EmailProvider {
    - smtpHost : String
    - fromAddress : String
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class SMSProvider {
    - apiKey : String
    - senderId : String
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class PushProvider {
    - fcmKey : String
    - apnsKey : String
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class InAppProvider {
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class WhatsAppProvider {
    - businessApiKey : String
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class SlackProvider {
    - webhookUrl : String
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class WebhookProvider {
    - targetUrl : String
    --
    + send(notification) : ProviderResult
    + getChannel() : ChannelType
}

class ProviderResult {
    - success : boolean
    - providerId : String
    - externalId : String
    - errorMessage : String
    - latencyMs : long
}

note bottom of ChannelProvider #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Deliver via the right channel.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — each channel is a
    pluggable provider. All implement send()."

    "**EmailProvider**: SMTP/SendGrid/SES.
    **SMSProvider**: Twilio/SNS.
    **PushProvider**: FCM (Android) + APNs (iOS).
    **InApp**: write to DB, show in bell icon.
    **WhatsApp**: Business API.
    **Slack/Webhook**: for integrations."

    "Add TelegramProvider? One new class.
    ProviderResult tracks success + latency."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

ChannelProvider <|.. EmailProvider
ChannelProvider <|.. SMSProvider
ChannelProvider <|.. PushProvider
ChannelProvider <|.. InAppProvider
ChannelProvider <|.. WhatsAppProvider
ChannelProvider <|.. SlackProvider
ChannelProvider <|.. WebhookProvider
ChannelProvider --> ProviderResult : returns >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: DISPATCHER + QUEUE — Prioritized Delivery
' ====================================================================
class NotificationDispatcher {
    - providerRegistry : Map<ChannelType, ChannelProvider>
    - queue : PriorityQueue<Notification>
    - maxConcurrent : int
    - fallbackRegistry : Map<ChannelType, ChannelProvider>
    --
    + dispatch(notification) : ProviderResult
    + enqueue(notification) : void
    + processQueue() : void
    + registerProvider(channel, provider) : void
    + registerFallback(channel, provider) : void
}

note bottom of NotificationDispatcher #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Prioritized dispatch.**
    "Notifications enter a PriorityQueue.
    CRITICAL OTPs processed immediately.
    MARKETING campaigns batched."

    "Dispatcher looks up the ChannelProvider
    for the notification's channel and calls
    send(). If primary provider fails, tries
    **fallback** (SendGrid down? Try SES).
    maxConcurrent limits parallel sends."
end note

NotificationDispatcher --> ChannelProvider : delivers via >
NotificationDispatcher o--> Notification : queues >
NotificationService --> NotificationDispatcher


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: RATE LIMITER — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface RateLimitStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + isAllowed(userId, eventType) : boolean
    + recordSend(userId, eventType) : void
}

class PerUserRateLimiter {
    - maxPerHour : int
    --
    + isAllowed(userId, eventType) : boolean
    + recordSend(userId, eventType) : void
}

class PerEventRateLimiter {
    - maxPerEventPerDay : Map<EventType, Integer>
    --
    + isAllowed(userId, eventType) : boolean
    + recordSend(userId, eventType) : void
}

class SlidingWindowRateLimiter {
    - windowMs : long
    - maxInWindow : int
    --
    + isAllowed(userId, eventType) : boolean
    + recordSend(userId, eventType) : void
}

class RateLimiter {
    - strategies : List<RateLimitStrategy>
    --
    + checkLimit(userId, eventType) : boolean
    + recordSend(userId, eventType) : void
}

note bottom of RateLimitStrategy #FFCDD2
    **STEP 8 - Don't spam the user.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — rate limiting
    is pluggable."

    "**PerUser**: max 20 notifications/hour.
    **PerEvent**: max 3 OTPs/day, 1 promo/day.
    **SlidingWindow**: max 5 in any 10-min window."

    "RateLimiter runs ALL strategies. If any
    says 'not allowed', notification is SUPPRESSED.
    Prevents notification fatigue."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

RateLimitStrategy <|.. PerUserRateLimiter
RateLimitStrategy <|.. PerEventRateLimiter
RateLimitStrategy <|.. SlidingWindowRateLimiter
RateLimiter o--> RateLimitStrategy : checks >
NotificationService --> RateLimiter


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: RETRY — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface RetryStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + shouldRetry(notification, attempt, error) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

class ExponentialBackoffRetry {
    - maxRetries : int
    - baseDelayMs : long
    --
    + shouldRetry(notification, attempt, error) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

class ImmediateRetry {
    - maxRetries : int
    --
    + shouldRetry(notification, attempt, error) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

class NoRetry {
    + shouldRetry(notification, attempt, error) : boolean
    + getDelayMs(attempt) : long
}

note bottom of RetryStrategy #FFCDD2
    **STEP 9 - Handle delivery failures.**
    "SMS provider timeout? Push token expired?"

    "**Strategy Pattern:**
    **ExponentialBackoff**: 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s.
    **ImmediateRetry**: retry once instantly
    (for transient network errors).
    **NoRetry**: marketing — don't bother.
    CRITICAL OTPs: immediate retry + fallback."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

RetryStrategy <|.. ExponentialBackoffRetry
RetryStrategy <|.. ImmediateRetry
RetryStrategy <|.. NoRetry
NotificationDispatcher --> RetryStrategy : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 10: DELIVERY TRACKING — Observer Pattern
' ====================================================================
class DeliveryTracker {
    - notifications : Map<String, Notification>
    - observers : List<DeliveryObserver>
    --
    + track(notification) : void
    + updateStatus(notificationId, status) : void
    + getStatus(notificationId) : DeliveryStatus
    + getMetrics(from, to) : DeliveryMetrics
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
}

interface DeliveryObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onDeliveryEvent(notification, oldStatus, newStatus) : void
}

class WebhookCallbackObserver {
    + onDeliveryEvent(notification, oldStatus, newStatus) : void
}

class MetricsObserver {
    + onDeliveryEvent(notification, oldStatus, newStatus) : void
}

class FailureAlertObserver {
    - failureThreshold : int
    --
    + onDeliveryEvent(notification, oldStatus, newStatus) : void
}

class AuditLogObserver {
    + onDeliveryEvent(notification, oldStatus, newStatus) : void
}

class DeliveryMetrics {
    - totalSent : long
    - totalDelivered : long
    - totalFailed : long
    - totalBounced : long
    - avgLatencyMs : double
    - deliveryRate : double
    --
    + getDeliveryRate() : double
}

note bottom of DeliveryObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 10 - Track everything.**
    "Every notification's delivery is tracked.
    **Observer Pattern** — on status change:"

    "**WebhookCallback**: notify caller service
    that their notification was delivered/failed.
    **MetricsObserver**: compute delivery rate,
    avg latency, bounce rate for dashboards.
    **FailureAlertObserver**: if failure rate
    spikes, alert the on-call engineer.
    **AuditLogObserver**: compliance trail."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

DeliveryObserver <|.. WebhookCallbackObserver
DeliveryObserver <|.. MetricsObserver
DeliveryObserver <|.. FailureAlertObserver
DeliveryObserver <|.. AuditLogObserver
DeliveryTracker --> DeliveryObserver : notifies >
DeliveryTracker --> Notification : tracks >
DeliveryTracker --> DeliveryMetrics : computes >
NotificationService --> DeliveryTracker


' ====================================================================
'  RESULT
' ====================================================================
class NotificationResult {
    - notificationId : String
    - status : DeliveryStatus
    - channelsSent : List<ChannelType>
    - channelsSuppressed : List<ChannelType>
    - suppressionReason : String
}

NotificationService --> NotificationResult : returns >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Service fires event -> NotificationService renders
    template per channel (**Template Strategy**) -> Router resolves
    channels via **Chain of Responsibility** (priority, user prefs,
    quiet hours) -> RateLimiter checks limits (**Rate Limit Strategy**)
    -> Dispatcher queues by priority, sends via **ChannelProvider**
    (**Strategy**: Email/SMS/Push/WhatsApp/Slack) -> Failure? **Retry
    Strategy** (backoff/immediate/none) + fallback provider -> Delivery
    tracked, observers notified (**Observer**: webhook, metrics, alerts).
    6 patterns: **Facade, Chain of Responsibility, Strategy (x5), Observer**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Any service calls NotificationService.send(request) | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | NotificationRequest: event type, recipient, priority, payload | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Notification: channel, content, status lifecycle, timestamps | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Render template per (event + channel + locale) | Strategy (template) | OCP, DIP |
    | 5 | Route: priority -> user prefs -> override -> quiet hours | Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP |
    | 6 | Deliver via Email / SMS / Push / InApp / WhatsApp / Slack | Strategy (channel) | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    | 7 | Priority queue: CRITICAL first, MARKETING last. Fallback on failure | -- | SRP |
    | 8 | Rate limit: per-user, per-event, sliding window | Strategy (rate limit) | OCP, SRP |
    | 9 | Retry: exponential backoff / immediate / none | Strategy (retry) | OCP |
    | 10 | Track delivery, webhook callback, metrics, failure alerts | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Render + Route** = Steps 4-5 | **Deliver** = Steps 6-7 | **Protect** = Steps 8-9 | **Track** = Step 10 |
endlegend

@enduml
